---

# Pathogenic Fungi Assignment Instructions

1. You will be assigned one fungal pathogen.  
2. Use **PubMed** (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov) to research your fungus.  
3. Answer the questions in each of the 9 categories provided in this slide set.  
4. Save your completed work in a **Word document (.docx)**.  
   - Title the file with your name and fungus (e.g., `JaneDoe_Histoplasma.docx`).  
5. Submit the Word document as directed.

---

# 1. Taxonomy & Classification
- **When/Who/Where** was it discovered?
- What phylum/class/order/family?  
- Is it a yeast, mold, dimorphic fungus, or dermatophyte?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Trichophyton rubrum taxonomy"`  
- `"Histoplasma capsulatum classification"`  
- `"Aspergillus fumigatus phylogeny"`  

---

# 2. Morphology & Life Cycle
- Growth form (yeast, hyphae, dimorphic)?  
- Sexual vs asexual reproduction?  
- Special structures (spores, conidia, asci, basidia)?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Candida albicans morphology life cycle"`  
- `"Sporothrix schenckii conidia"`  
- `"Blastomyces dermatitidis dimorphic fungus"`  

---

# 3. Ecology & Reservoirs
- Natural environment (soil, caves, plants, animals, human skin)?  
- Conditions favoring growth (temperature, pH, moisture)?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Coccidioides immitis soil ecology"`  
- `"Pseudogymnoascus destructans bat caves reservoir"`  
- `"Paracoccidioides ecology reservoir"`  

---

# 4. Mode of Transmission
- How do people/animals acquire infection?  
- Inhalation, direct contact, trauma, ingestion?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Microsporum audouinii transmission"`  
- `"Histoplasma capsulatum inhalation spores"`  
- `"Candida albicans opportunistic infection"`  

---

# 5. Pathogenesis & Clinical Disease
- What disease(s) does it cause?  
- Which tissues/organs are targeted?  
- Key virulence factors (toxins, enzymes, immune evasion)?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Aspergillus fumigatus pathogenesis lung"`  
- `"Trichophyton rubrum dermatophytosis"`  
- `"Blastomyces dermatitidis virulence factors"`  

---

# 6. Epidemiology
- Geographic distribution (tropical, temperate, arid)?  
- Endemic vs worldwide?  
- Populations at risk?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Histoplasma capsulatum epidemiology Mississippi Valley"`  
- `"Coccidioides immitis Valley Fever epidemiology"`  
- `"Talaromyces marneffei epidemiology HIV"`  

---

# 7. Diagnosis
- Clinical signs/symptoms  
- Lab methods (microscopy, culture, PCR, histology, serology)  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Candida albicans diagnosis PCR culture"`  
- `"Sporothrix schenckii diagnosis biopsy"`  
- `"Paracoccidioides brasiliensis serological diagnosis"`  

---

# 8. Treatment & Control
- Common antifungals (azoles, amphotericin B, echinocandins)  
- Resistance issues?  
- Prevention measures (PPE, avoiding exposure, healthcare strategies)?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Aspergillus fumigatus antifungal resistance"`  
- `"Candidiasis treatment fluconazole echinocandin"`  
- `"Histoplasmosis amphotericin itraconazole treatment"`  

---

# 9. Relevance & Impact
- Why is this fungus important?  
- Human health, agriculture, ecology, or economy?  

**PubMed Search Terms**  
- `"Candida albicans global burden health"`  
- `"Pseudogymnoascus destructans white nose syndrome impact"`  
- `"Aspergillus fumigatus agriculture contamination"`  
